title_container.heading: Success Stories
title_container.paragraph: Hear from some of our graduates and the managers that hired them in the videos below.

title_container_1.heading: Software Engineering Talent
title_container_1.paragraph: Look no further for top-trained and vetted talent to hire

carousel.title: Jarue Johnson
carousel.content: From hardware repair to Platform Engineer at Watsco

carousel.title: Skarzold Bellingar
carousel.content: From shift manager at Pizza Hut to Senior Team Lead at GRUBBRR

carousel.title: Adrian Perdomo
carousel.content: From waiter to Mobile Developer at RockVal

alumni.title: Joelle Johnson
alumni.content: Former Retail Manager and CS Major
alumni.description: Having led in management for three years, Joelle's pivot to real estate led her to a fascination with data analytics. It was this intrigue that nudged her towards pursuing computer programming. Her forte lies in full stack development, particularly backend technologies, data manipulation, and security. An outgoing and team-driven individual, Joelle thrives on conquering new challenges. Outside of coding, Joelle is passionate about nature, family, and community outreach.
alumni.final_project_description: Don't know what to get your loved ones for that special occasion? Check out their wishlist on WishLily!

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I chose Boca Code because I love coding. I felt that I was not learning at a satisfactory pace in college. I was able to code, but unable to engineer. I had no portfolio to showcase, and I wanted to be employable, quickly. I was hungry to learn how to make functioning full-stack apps, and Boca Code was a great way for me to hone my skills and become employable. I felt confident that Boca Code could fill in the gaps of information and leave me with a strong resume, portfolio, and network.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Knowing how to network, manage time, and problem solve.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: A friend of mine was a young web developer, and he was financially independent and had a great work-life balance. I took the plunge, tried coding on my own at home, fell in love with it and pursued a degree in computer programming.

alumni.title: Andy Arias
alumni.description: I'm a 20-year-old Cuban, very enthusiastic and charismatic. I love learning new things and I'm passionate about programming. I have a keen interest in most technology fields. I'm known for being a very sociable and helpful person with many friends. I enjoy meeting new people and assisting others. I love working in a team and appreciate an organized work environment.
alumni.final_project_description: Sugar Smart is an app developed to help people with diabetes accurately store and track their blood-sugar levels.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: Boca Code was the best option in Coral Springs, even while being in Boca Raton, then when i met the crew I felt like I was with family.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Being persistent and responsible is the key to achieving what you set out to do.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: My desire to improve my lifestyle and passion for technology.

alumni.title: Evelybenson Chatelain
alumni.description: I'm Evelybenson Chatelain. I am 23 years old and currently studying software engineering at Boca Code. Before that, I lived in Haiti (5 months ago), where I was a civil engineer, a graphic designer, a musician, a passionate creative, and love to combine art and code.
alumni.final_project_description: IMCONA = Immigrant Connect App / It's an immigration app that simplifies your experience by helping you locate service offices such as Social Security, driver's license, and immigration services in the United States. Plan your visits easily and manage your schedules with our user-friendly tool.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I chose Boca Code because I received a lot of positive feedback about the school and because I want to become a real software engineer. I think it's the best place to learn to code.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: I think you must have: Programming Language Proficiency / Understanding of Fundamental Concepts / Problem-Solving Skills / Development Tool Mastery / Curiosity and Continuous Learning / Effective Communication / Teamwork / Testing and Debugging /

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: In reality I am always in search of knowledge... when I arrived in the United States I wanted to learn some really exciting things because I am passionate about art and creation and I chose coding because I love it.

alumni.title: Tremayne L. Johnson
alumni.description: Strong Work Ethic - Grounded Character - Very Resilient To Defeatist Mentality
alumni.final_project_tittle: The Mayne Course Recipe Builder and Events Calendar
alumni.final_project_description: I built an Events Calendar where users can plan out any kind of event (weddings-birthdays-holidays) and either connect with catering vendors or use and find recipes on their own. The user will be able to search and build full course meals as well as create and share their own recipes.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I choose Boca Code because after my initial research into the school, not only did I find out they were the Platinum Standard in Florida Coding Boot Camps, their success rate is also very high. They have turned many regular people into awesome Engineers.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Diligence - Constant Education - Trail & Error

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: I needed a Industry that would allow me to learn and keep learning without a ceiling. Also a trucking accident has left me not being able to drive trucks anymore. Also the pay compares and exceeds what I was earning in trucking.

alumni.title: John Savin
alumni.description: I am a servant leader to an amazing wife and 3 young boys who together have pushed me to evolve personally and professionally. Over the past 3 decades, I dedicated my career to working across three industries with play a major role in our lives - health, home and wealth. In 2022, my desire to pivot into tech grew seeing how influential it is in our lives. Being able to positively shape the way people use tech motivated me to take the plunge.
alumni.final_project_description: A fun and interactive adventure as 3 young Dino Hunters learn about dinosaurs of the past and discover new imaginative species of the future.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: After 18 months deciding to pivot my career into tech, I decided to attend Boca Code because it provided a much needed structure and an in-depth, well-rounded curriculum. Being new to software engineering, I became overwhelmed navigating which skills to learn and programs to study. Boca Code focused my efforts with the tools and mentoring needed to break into this industry.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: In wealth management, it is vital to be a highly communicative problem solver and figure of strength with your clients and team. Our solutions must be tailored to client needs and nimble to evolve as personal circumstances or market environments change.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: Over my 30 plus year career I have chosen industries that have a direct impact on people - their health, home, and in 2001 personal finance. Upon seeing my parents struggle financially I dedicated the next two decades as a wealth manager so I can assist my family and others sharing similar challenges.

alumni.title: Alex Artemov
alumni.description: Alex, a multilingual software engineer with a journalism and scriptwriting background, holds advanced Advertising and PR degrees. His expertise in media monitoring, content production, and strategic communication, combined with a passion for technology, drives him to constantly explore programming languages and digital tools.
alumni.final_project_description: Tale Together is a collaborative story-writing platform designed to develop original stories and bring joy to aspiring writers.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: Boca Code's 10-week course offers a fast and practical approach to break into the tech sector and kickstart your career.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Curiosity and perseverance.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: Vast opportunities to impact lives and shape a better future.

alumni.title: Micado Pierre
alumni.description: Born and raised in the vibrant Broward County, Florida, Micado embodies a unique blend of passions and expertise. A seasoned realtor with an eye for detail and a knack for understanding clients' needs, Micado has cultivated a reputation for integrity, dedication, and unparalleled service in the ever-evolving real estate landscape of South Florida. Beyond the world of property and negotiations, Micado leads a parallel life as a software engineer, navigating the intricate realm of coding, innovation, and technological advancements. With a penchant for problem-solving and a creative mind, Micado thrives in crafting elegant solutions to complex digital challenges. Even while excelling in the dynamic realms of real estate and technology, Micado has set their sights on a different horizon medicine. Currently pursuing a pre-medical education, Micado is fueled by a passion for understanding the human body and a desire to contribute to healthcare in meaningful ways. Juggling the worlds of business, technology, and medicine, Micado embraces the challenge with the same enthusiasm that defines their work ethic. In the moments between demanding schedules, you'll often find Micado on the basketball court, where the love for the game is nurtured. A dedicated player and a team enthusiast, basketball serves as a sanctuary, a place to unwind, strategize, and connect with others beyond the professional realms. With a multifaceted background and an unwavering commitment to growth and learning, Micado epitomizes the spirit of versatility and determination, showcasing the endless possibilities that arise from embracing diverse passions and pursuing multiple paths in life.
alumni.final_project_description: Never Miss A Stat: Introducing the Ultimate NBA Statistics App. Elevate your basketball fandom to a whole new level with the ZBSPORTS app your one-stop shop for all things NBA stats!

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I choose Boca Code to become a great Software Engineer.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: The most important skill is to be persistent and always be learning.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: The thing that inspired me to pursue the current career path is because that I have a love of amazing and beautiful homes.

alumni.title: Michael Fisher
alumni.description: After 15 years as a hairstylist and platform educator for a world-renowned company, Michael's insatiable curiosity propelled him into the cutting-edge realms of Web3, Blockchain, and Artificial Intelligence. Now, as a full-stack developer, he leverages his meticulous attention to detail, unwavering dedication, and relentless pursuit of knowledge to craft innovative solutions that bridge the gap between art and technology. Infusing his unique blend of artistic sensitivity and passion for innovation, he fuels his vision to shape the future of technology, scale businesses and brands, and empower others through groundbreaking advancements.
alumni.final_project_description: Full-stack app for tracking things like watering schedule, fertilization, and adding new tropical plants.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: Because of its full-time in person course, great reviews, and senior level developers.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Having the ability to build full-stack applications, drive for knowledge, staying ahead of the trends, and understanding of how to scale businesses and brands.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: For my love of blockchain, web3 and the thirst for knowledge.

alumni.title: Gino Guerra
alumni.description: I'm a very passionate videogame dev that loves creating.
alumni.final_project_description: A web application that describes new games genres and more information

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I've looked into a lot of bootcamps and this was the only one that asked me questions and made sure I was determined and that I wanted to do this and that made me feel like they really care about the students and their education.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Knowing Unity, C#, C++, Unreal Engine 5

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: I loved videogames and I've always wanted to be apart of it more than just playing.

alumni.title: Max Espinosa
alumni.description: Max spent two years studying Culinary Arts. At school, she was in robotics, IT, and STEM classes, fueling her love for technology and problem-solving. She loves CSS, crafting visually appealing web designs. Besides coding, she finds pleasure in helping those around me and animals in need.
alumni.final_project_description: Discover and track animals. Share info, and reunite lost pets with their owners while supporting adorable strays.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I chose Boca Code because it was recommended to me by my brother Eddie. He told me about how amazing everyone was and how much he had learned in such a little amount of time.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Patience, problem solving, analytic thinking, creativity, and communication skills.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: The high demand for tech, attractive pay, and comfort with computers.

alumni.title: John Cadet Therlonge
alumni.description: John is a mix of tech and gaming enthusiast, alongside exceptional cooking abilities. His strong desire to help others and passion for learning are striking. With nine years of experience in inventory management, John has a solid track record of improving complex logistical processes. This diverse skill set makes him well-suited for roles that combine his tech know-how, culinary talent, people-friendly nature, and operational expertise.
alumni.final_project_description: Pocket Binder is a personal and professional inventory tracker.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: The 10 week course that Boca Code provide is a very quick and efficient way to take a step towards the tech world and future career.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: The ability to learn and be coachable, perseverance and hard work.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: The economy is taking a nose dive and acquiring a skill such coding is irreplaceable in the job market.

alumni.title: Andrew Wilborn
alumni.description: A recent graduate of UCF with a degree in Computer Science, Andrew is armed with additional training and certification from Boca Code as a full stack software engineer. Andrew is passionate about learning new technologies and expanding his skillset.
alumni.final_project_description: A platform for Magic The Gathering players to communicate and provide feedback on the power of eachothers decks.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I came to Boca Code to deepen my understanding of software engineering and grow my skillset. It has enabled me to build upon the strong foundation I obtained at UCF and grow from merely a strong coder into a fully fledged software engineer.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Proper planning and communication with your team is the most important skill in software engineering. This will allow teams to be organized and consistent which is key to a successful project.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: Ever since I first learned how to code when I was a teenager I've known that I want to be a software engineer. I love what I do and I think I'm pretty darn good at it too.

alumni.title: Daniel Lancheros
alumni.description: Top-notch software engineer with a mindset geared towards creative solutions. Daniel has transitioned from a successful salesperson and logistics analyst to pursue his passion for technology with a new challenge. He is embarking on a journey into the intricate world of technical coding.
alumni.final_project_description: A web application designed for creating events to share with family and friends.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I wanted to challenge myself with a new skill combining with my love for technology.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Passion to learn, being a team player, setting and completing goals, problem solving.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: Seeing the rise with technology over the years and wanting to be involved in innovation.

alumni.title: Kevin Fernandez
alumni.description: Kevin is a driven problem solver with a passion for cars. He loves learning new things and thrives on challenges. With his adaptability and dedication, he excels in dynamic environments, constantly seeking opportunities to grow and find innovative solutions.
alumni.final_project_description: A carpooling app that connects drivers and passengers, enabling them to share rides to a common destination.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I chose Boca Code because it offered a practical, hands-on learning experience for my career transition into the tech industry. The bootcamp's shorter duration, supportive environment, and job placement assistance were essential factors in my decision.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Problem-solving, continuous learning, and collaboration are crucial components needed to succeed in this field.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: I was inspired to pursue my current career due to my passion for technology, problem-solving, the opportunity to make an impact, and the flexibility and collaboration in the field.

alumni.title: Lorenzo Mokwa
alumni.description: Lorenzo was born and raised in Brazil and developed a passion for computers from a very young age. He finds enjoyment in overcoming challenges and loves to discover the intricacies and nuances of computer hardware and software. Lorenzo was a former computer science student who decided test and develop his skills by joining Boca Code.
alumni.final_project_description: Collector's Car Hub is a user-curated marketplace built for enthusiasts, by enthusiasts. The platform allows users to share and rate car listings from different platforms across the web.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: The variety of the coursework provided was a deciding factor for me. Being exposed to multiple technologies and practices seen in the workplace was extremely valuable and helped me develop a strong foundation as a software engineer. The curriculum made it very easy to break the 'entry barrier' into coding, making the experience smooth but challenging.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: Being flexible and open-minded, in addition to having problem solving and critical thinking skills, are some of the most important skills for a successful software engineer.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: Because I grew up around computers, a computer-related career always seemed the obvious choice for a career path. From a young age, I've always loved building and taking computers apart. After recently finding the same passion for computer software, and seeing the continuously growing field of software engineering, I decided to pursue it as a career.

alumni.title: Yaslin Carmona
alumni.description: With a decade in financial sales, including two years in sales training, Yaslin transitioned to freelance front-end development. Driven by a thirst for knowledge and technology passion, she shifted towards full-stack engineering, enrolling in Boca Code. This shift blends her customer-centric background with technical expertise for impactful contributions to software engineering.
alumni.final_project_description: My project involves developing a comprehensive file manager and agenda organizer. This application aims to provide efficient file management capabilities along with an intuitive agenda system to help users stay organized and productive.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I chose Boca Code because of my initial positive experience with frontend development. I was drawn to the field and wanted to expand my knowledge to become a proficient full-stack engineer. Additionally, I saw it as a valuable opportunity to learn the latest technologies in the industry.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: In my field, a combination of technical proficiency, effective communication, adaptability, and problem-solving skills are crucial for achieving success.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: The inspiration behind my current career path stems from the quest for job security, a factor I found lacking in my previous profession. Additionally, witnessing the enduring passion that individuals have for their work, even after two decades, played a pivotal role in motivating me. The desire to create something impactful and meaningful further ignited my journey.

alumni.title: Jeniffer Giraldo
alumni.description: I am software engineer with a diverse background in teaching and education, skilled in critical thinking and problem-solving. Passionate about leveraging technology to enhance lives and make a positive impact. Lifelong learner eager to contribute to meaningful projects.
alumni.final_project_description: My project is dedicated to exploring the growing popularity of mocktails, the non-alcoholic alternatives to traditional cocktails. It delves into the reasons behind their rise, particularly focusing on health consciousness, the significance of designated drivers, inclusivity, and the creative potential they offer. By featuring a wide array of mocktail recipes and informative content, Sip Savvy Mocktails aims to encourage healthier lifestyle choices, promote overall public safety, and foster an inclusive environment for those opting to abstain from alcohol. The website celebrates the delightful and satisfying nature of mocktails, highlighting their complexity and visual appeal. Through this project, I aim to contribute to a responsible and enjoyable social drinking culture, where mocktails play a positive and exciting role.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: The small class sizes and project-based learning approach appealed to me, as it allows for personalized attention and practical skills development. Additionally, the positive reviews and success stories from alumni motivated me to overcome my initial intimidation and pursue my interest in coding.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: The most important skill for success in the tech industry as a software engineer is adaptability. It will allow me to connect my teaching expertise with the technical skills required in software engineering. Embracing adaptability will help me thrive in this field and making a successful transition into the tech industry.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: The pursuit of a career in the tech field is driven by the need for financial stability and a passion for utilizing technology to benefit teachers, students, and parents. As an educator, I am constantly formulating creative ideas, but unfortunately, my current profession lacks the support to bring them to fruition. Transitioning into the tech industry presents an exciting opportunity to explore and implement my ideas freely, fostering ingenuity and empowering creativity. I am eager to blend my existing skills with technology, making a significant impact on education while also enjoying improved financial prospects and personal growth in this ever-changing field.

alumni.title: Kevin Dietmeyer
alumni.description: Prior to becoming a software engineer, Kevin was a software account manager with a leading technology company, where he excelled in business development, customer relationship management, and sales. In the finance space, he coached and mentored top-performing sales representatives and teams, achieving record-breaking results. He has a deep understanding of the health and fitness industry, having worked as a personal trainer and nutrition professional for more than a decade.
alumni.final_project_description: Hang From the Bar generates a unique workout for the user with the push of a button. A built in timer keeps track of the total workout time and upon submit the users workout and final time are logged for future reference so they can view their hard work and progress.

qa.title: Why Boca Code?
qa.answer: I chose Boca Code because I wanted to learn the latest technologies and best practices from leading experts in the field.

qa.title: What are some of the important skills for success in your field?
qa.answer: The most important skill for success is finding opportunity in every obstacle.

qa.title: What inspired you to pursue your current career path?
qa.answer: I was inspired to pursue a career in technology after being exposed to the field while working in enterprise software sales. I had the opportunity to work with a lot of engineers and I decided to pursue a career path in software.
